The President convened a call with members of his Cabinet, state and local officials, and senior members of his team to receive a briefing on ongoing response and recovery efforts. He received updates on severe weather moving into the affected region and efforts to address power and fuel challenges. The President spoke to Governor Cuomo, Governor Malloy, and other officials about potential challenges and directed his team to provide additional support for preparations ahead of the severe weather. Secretary of Labor Hilda Solis, Secretary of Energy Steven Chu, and Secretary Napolitano traveled to the affected region to meet with business owners, volunteers, and affected individuals, and discuss ongoing response and recovery efforts. Secretary Napolitano also announced additional funding for debris removal efforts in Connecticut, New Jersey, and New York. Tomorrow, Secretary Napolitano will travel to New York to hold meetings and view response activities.